snippet.textDisplay: Most songs of ***** India are very beautiful in essence. But somehow I feel the thrills and frills are always used too liberally, possibly to make them more 'catchy', so to speak. I wish they would respect the core values of the music and the musicians, keep it raw and simple. Fusion is one thing and over-the top adorning is another.'Less is more' never failed, never will. Lack of confidence in raw authentic genres,voices and sounds does not really promote Indian music scene.
